description.narrative: (Bangladesh): The MaMoni Health Systems Strengthening (MaMoni-HSS) activity supports the Ministry of Health and Family Welfare (MOHFW) to improve the utilization of integrated maternal, newborn, and child health; family planning; and nutrition services, and strengthens the health systems to support service delivery. USAID will use FY 2017 funds to support national level effort to harmonize the job descriptions of community health workers (CHWs) in the public and NGO sectors, and identify modalities to generate community and local government support to improving CHW performance. The activity will simultaneously work with NIPORT, to prepare for the rapid roll out of a harmonized package of capacity-building inputs for the CHWs, their first line supervisors and sub-district level managers. USAID support will contribute to developing an institutional capacity for training of community health workers, service providers, managers, and community members to strengthen the health systems.
